  "worklog": "# brainTrade Work Log\n*Check this anytime to see what I'm doing and how I'm thinking.*\n\n---\n\n## 2026-04-22 01:45 UTC \u2014 [P4: Alpha Research] 01h Looks Like a Noisy Battleground, Not a Quiet Follow-Through Edge\n\n**Task:** Re-examine 01h with more live data to determine whether it is simply weaker than midnight or whether it has its own distinct structure that still deserves attention.\n**Finding:**\n- Both bots are alive and PM remains flat outside active hours.\n- 01h is not dead, but it is structurally messy:\n  - total tracked 01h windows: **44**\n  - price regimes:\n    - `(0.505, 0.495)` \u2192 **29** windows, `14` with `|bias| >= 45`, `7` with `|bias| >= 55`, max `70.1`\n    - `(0.515, 0.485)` \u2192 **10** windows, `6` with `|bias| >= 45`, `4` with `|bias| >= 55`, max `69.5`\n    - `(0.485, 0.515)` \u2192 **5** windows, only `1` with `|bias| >= 45`, `0` with `|bias| >= 55`, max `54.9`\n  - total regime flips observed: **3**\n- So 01h does produce forceful moves, but the session is fragmented across competing price states rather than expressing a clean, persistent edge.\n- PM copy flow also looks indecisive and expensive rather than informative:\n  - recent signals: **25 bullish / 25 bearish**\n  - average price **0.949**\n  - dominant prints are split between opposing crowd behaviors:\n    - `SELL Up @ 0.99` (15x)\n    - `BUY Down @ 0.85` (15x)\n    - `BUY Down @ 0.997` (10x)\n- That is not confirmation. It is crowd conflict at rich prices.\n\n**My thinking:**\nThis sharpens the overnight map. Midnight looked active-but-unstable. 01h now looks like a **noisy battleground**: strong enough to tempt, but structurally split and paired with conflicting crowd behavior. That is exactly the kind of regime that can generate impressive-looking bias prints without delivering a robust tradeable edge.\n\n**Decision:**\n- Keep 01h excluded.\n- Strengthen the reason: not merely \u201cweaker than 00h,\u201d but \u201ctoo structurally noisy and conflicted.\u201d\n- Keep PM copy flow classified as crowd-state texture, especially when it splits cleanly into opposing rich prints.\n\n**Next:** If 01h keeps appearing active on future nights, compare directional persistence window-by-window. If strong 01h bias repeatedly fails to hold a single dominant regime, that becomes durable evidence for permanent exclusion.\n\n---\n## 2026-04-22 01:29 UTC \u2014 [P3: Strategy Development] V7d Overnight Boundary Spec Written\n\n**Task:** Prevent overnight watchlist creep by turning the new 00h vs 01h evidence into an explicit boundary spec.\n**Finding:**\n- Both bots are alive and PM remains out of active hours.\n- I wrote `/home/ubuntu/clawd/patches/v7d-overnight-boundary.spec.md`.\n- The spec formalizes the overnight stance:\n  - **00h** = watchlist / shadow-validation candidate only\n  - **01h** = excluded\n- It also explicitly blocks sloppy \u201covernight bucket\u201d thinking by requiring 00h and 01h to be logged and judged separately.\n\n**My thinking:**\nThis is the right P3 move because strategy sprawl usually happens at the boundary. Once one excluded hour",
